Ogun State  –  Many notable dignitaries attended the opening of the Olusegun Obasanjo’s Presidential Library in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital yesterday. The former President was joined by national leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Bola Tinubu, ex-President, Goodluck Jonathan, ex-Head of State, Abdulsalami Abubakar. Others include, current President of Liberia, Ellen Johnson Sirleaf , Peoples Democratic Party National Chairman, Ali Modu Sheriff, Governor of Lagos State, Akinwumi Ambode, Senator Godswill Akpabio, Senator Ben Bruce and others. See photos below… 